30
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:44,660
You met the husband of my mom in Canada, remember?

31
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:48,110
Ah!

32
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,340
So,

33
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:11,070
your answer is?

34
00:03:12,370 --> 00:03:14,140
No...

35
00:03:14,140 --> 00:03:17,220
Your answer is not important anyway.

36
00:03:17,220 --> 00:03:21,860
Regardless of what other people say, I'm going to marry Da Da.

37
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:25,320
Marriage is not just between two people who like each other.

38
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:30,400
I know that even if you don't teach me. Who would say you're not a teach?

39
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:32,440
Teacher.

40
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:35,640
You still don't know after I taught you that.

41
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:38,800
Yes, Teacher.

42
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:43,760
Don't think so seriously.

43
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:47,010
It's also not something to think lightly of.

44
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:56,630
Do you want to see me marrying another woman and living well?

45
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:03,070
I don't like it either. Seeing you with another man,

46
00:04:03,070 --> 00:04:06,190
me with another woman...

47
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:10,570
I don't know about you but I was not okay at all.

48
00:04:11,890 --> 00:04:14,580
I wasn't okay either.

49
00:04:16,090 --> 00:04:20,560
Then stay with me. Let's stay together.

50
00:04:22,790 --> 00:04:27,260
Other people break up because they fall out of love.

51
00:04:27,260 --> 00:04:30,530
But we love each other, so why should we break up?

52
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:35,850
What did you just say?

53
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:40,790
I love you, Da Hyeon.

54
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:54,230
What's wrong?

55
00:04:55,750 --> 00:04:57,860
You jerk!

56
00:04:57,860 --> 00:05:01,030
Why are you telling me that now?
♫ I’ll only shine for you ♫

57
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:07,070
♫ I’ll only whisper to you ♫

58
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:15,300
I can't quit my job and get approval from our families.
♫ I will be the smile ♫

59
00:05:16,790 --> 00:05:17,600
Pardon?

60
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:21,580
I can tolerate everything that you mentioned.

61
00:05:21,580 --> 00:05:25,190
But I can't let go of those two things no matter how hard I think about it.

62
00:05:25,190 --> 00:05:28,120
I worked hard for 10 years to be a teacher.

63
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:31,220
So I'm going to work for at least 10 years more before I consider quitting.

64
00:05:31,220 --> 00:05:34,760
Okay, that's fine.

65
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:37,140
I'm just worried that it will be hard on you.

66
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:38,940
I'll tell you if it gets too hard.

67
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:44,350
And even if you help me... no matter how much you help me,

68
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:50,520
I'm not that confident to marry into a family that doesn't want me. So you get approval from your family.

69
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:54,620
So then you want to marry me?

70
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,330
You're serious, right?

71
00:06:01,330 --> 00:06:05,360
I mean, you already said yes. No take-backs!

72
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:07,070
Yeah.

73
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:16,840
I love you, too.

74
00:06:29,260 --> 00:06:31,140
You're not leaving?

75
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:33,020
Can I sleep here tonight?

76
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:35,470
No...

77
00:06:35,470 --> 00:06:38,720
We're going to live together anyway once we get married.

78
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:42,110
Who knows what will happen? When we marry, we'll have married.

79
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:49,620
So are you saying you won't marry me?

80
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:52,160
I will. I said I would.

81
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,950
But after we get both families' approvals.

82
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:56,440
I will take care of that.

83
00:07:00,890 --> 00:07:06,240
I haven't slept much at all... couldn't you let me sleep over?

84
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:12,530
Indeed, your company is an odd one. Not letting people sleep.

85
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,770
Go home and sleep soon.

86
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:19,070
This time, I couldn't sleep because of you.

87
00:07:19,070 --> 00:07:23,160
Just be next to me... That's the only way I can sleep.

88
00:07:41,020 --> 00:07:48,450
Well... there are no clothes to change into, so it might be uncomfortable.

89
00:07:48,450 --> 00:07:51,450
It's not too late for you to go home and...

90
00:08:38,050 --> 00:08:39,660
Is that mine?

91
00:08:39,660 --> 00:08:41,880
Ah, you woke up?

92
00:08:53,230 --> 00:08:55,150
It's really you.

93
00:08:55,150 --> 00:08:58,760
You... what are you talking about?

94
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:02,860
I thought it was a dream... again.

95
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:11,500
It's not a dream.

96
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:21,930
I don't think so, either.

97
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:24,830
What a relief.

98
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,880
I'm sleepy.

99
00:09:29,710 --> 00:09:34,700
♫ Like the sunshine early in the morning  ♫

100
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:43,510
♫ You spread inside me, my heart is filled ♫

101
00:09:43,510 --> 00:09:50,130
♫ with the color of you.
Falling in love with you ♫

102
00:09:50,130 --> 00:09:54,950
♫ Like the scent of flowers in the spring ♫

103
00:09:54,950 --> 00:09:58,990
♫ that keeps tickling me ♫

104
00:10:04,610 --> 00:10:07,220
What brings you here so early?

105
00:10:07,220 --> 00:10:08,980
Mother.

106
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:13,400
Your son has a favor to ask.

107
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:23,660
What is it? My son looks very tense.

108
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:26,180
Are you worried because of the general stockholders meeting next month?

109
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:28,890
Don't worry about it. I already spoke with your maternal grandfather and—

110
00:10:28,890 --> 00:10:33,250
I can't give up Da Hyeon.

111
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:39,970
That child... are you back with her?

112
00:10:39,970 --> 00:10:42,400
No, not yet.

113
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,920
I want to get your approval first.

114
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,460
But what if I don't approve?

115
00:10:46,460 --> 00:10:50,190
Well, then I'll just grow old alone,

116
00:10:50,190 --> 00:10:51,580
and I'll make her do the same.

117
00:10:51,580 --> 00:10:53,350
Is that what that girl suggested?

118
00:10:53,350 --> 00:10:57,180
No, but it has to be like that.

119
00:10:57,180 --> 00:11:03,930
I don't think I can watch her marry another man,

120
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:05,880
so I can't let that happen.

121
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:08,640
Don't you think it will be hard?

122
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:10,600
We split up once...

123
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:17,000
And I thought I was dying... without her by my side.

124
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,500
Anything would be better than that.

125
00:11:28,850 --> 00:11:31,780
Do... do I look okay?

126
00:11:31,780 --> 00:11:33,590
Yeah, pretty.

127
00:11:33,590 --> 00:11:36,520
No, seriously. Look at me properly. Do I really look okay?

128
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:38,590
Yeah, seriously. You look good.

129
00:11:38,590 --> 00:11:42,640
And it's fine even if you don't. I'm not letting you go no matter what.

130
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:46,850
Oh, so it's not okay? I knew it. I should have worn something else... This is too big right?

131
00:11:46,850 --> 00:11:49,800
What are you listening to?

132
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:53,510
You really look pretty.

133
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:57,140
What are you two doing here?

134
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:02,440
Son, aren't you overdoing it?

135
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,790
Hello.

136
00:12:14,620 --> 00:12:17,620
Welcome. It's been a while.

137
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:22,560
It's my first time seeing you.

138
00:12:23,830 --> 00:12:25,930
You really don't know him?

139
00:12:26,730 --> 00:12:28,360
I told you!

140
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:32,860
You are my lifesaver.

141
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:35,190
Pardon?

142
00:12:35,190 --> 00:12:38,420
What... did I do?

143
00:12:38,420 --> 00:12:41,210
I'm indebted to you.

144
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,900
[Outpatient Clinic: Medical Bill - Receipt]

145
00:12:59,330 --> 00:13:01,140
You really don't remember?

146
00:13:02,130 --> 00:13:04,050
No...

147
00:13:04,570 --> 00:13:06,750
[Outpatient Clinic: Medical Bill - Receipt]

148
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:10,770
No, you are my lifesaver.

149
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,460
Something really bad could've happened to you on that day.

150
00:13:25,460 --> 00:13:28,470
I would've died if it hadn't been Da Hyeon.

151
00:13:28,470 --> 00:13:33,760
Therefore it's right that all of my money should go to Da Hyeon...

152
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:35,770
And the bad guy over there, he comes as the throw-in.

153
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:38,170
Grandpa.

154
00:13:38,170 --> 00:13:41,180
Get them married quickly, before I die.

155
00:13:41,180 --> 00:13:42,320
Yes, Father-in-law.

156
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:45,240
But Jae In is probably in more of a hurry than you, Father-in-law.

157
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:47,340
Yes, I'm getting very impatient, Mother.

158
00:13:47,340 --> 00:13:49,540
Jae In.

159
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:56,570
What do your parents like?

160
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:58,570
An oriental medicine doctor as the son-in-law.

161
00:13:59,980 --> 00:14:02,100
- You are an only child, right?
- Yeah.

162
00:14:03,070 --> 00:14:09,650
Then your parent's only son-in-law should be a man who works at the Seong Hyeon Group, no matter what.

163
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:14,800
His name is Lee Jae In. Sorry but it's impossible for them to get an oriental medicine doctor as their son-in-law.

164
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:21,000
What is this?

165
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,820
You're laughing?

166
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:29,590
Marriage? Absolutely not!

167
00:14:29,590 --> 00:14:34,450
Of course not. You said this was just business.

168
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:38,820
At first it started with a contract, but not anymore.

169
00:14:38,820 --> 00:14:42,790
I will take good care of her and we will live well together, cherishing each other.

170
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:45,730
Please allow this marriage.

171
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:50,700
Da Hyeon, I want you to marry an average man.

172
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:53,710
It doesn't have to be an oriental medicine doctor.

173
00:14:54,990 --> 00:14:57,680
Jae In is a good man.

174
00:14:57,680 --> 00:15:00,790
And I like him too.

175
00:15:00,790 --> 00:15:04,520
People always like each other in the beginning. That's how they marry.

176
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:08,370
But things are different once they start living together.

177
00:15:08,370 --> 00:15:13,180
Especially, when people are totally different, it gets harder and more tiring.

178
00:15:14,690 --> 00:15:18,450
I'm sorry but I don't want to see my daughter suffer.

179
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:20,860
Marriage? It doesn't have to be done so hastily.

180
00:15:20,860 --> 00:15:24,840
Meet many other men and marry when you're over 30.

181
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:27,120
It definitely cannot work with you two.

182
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:43,560
Jin Ju Oriental Medicine Clinic

183
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,220
What do we do?

184
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:47,380
Yeah...

185
00:15:47,380 --> 00:15:49,250
Do you just want to run away?

186
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:51,500
We can also try for a baby (before marriage).

187
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:54,080
Ugh, really.

188
00:15:55,820 --> 00:16:01,460
Should we listen to my dad and take it slowly? It's not like we are in a rush.

189
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,750
I'm feeling the rush though.

190
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:05,420
Jae In.

191
00:16:05,420 --> 00:16:09,460
Don't worry. I'm going to get his approval no matter what.

192
00:16:09,460 --> 00:16:11,870
As long as your feelings don't change, everything will be okay.

193
00:16:34,990 --> 00:16:40,920
Jinju 2 km

194
00:16:46,060 --> 00:16:47,920
Who is it?

195
00:16:49,930 --> 00:16:53,720
Ah yes, this is Lee Jae In who visited you with Da Hyeon last time.

196
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,970
Sorry, please leave.
(speaking formally throughout)

197
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:57,680
Wait.

198
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:26,560
You are here again.

199
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:31,350
Yes, Mother. I want to meet you in person today. I have something to tell you.

200
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:34,760
Even if you keep doing this, nothing will change.

201
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:37,060
I'm sorry.

202
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,650
He's here again, Da Hyeon's man.

203
00:18:00,650 --> 00:18:02,330
Who's Da Hyeon's man?

204
00:18:02,330 --> 00:18:04,140
The whole neighborhood already knows.

205
00:18:04,140 --> 00:18:07,240
He's so busy, but he keeps on coming over here as if he's our next-door neighbor.

206
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,680
I've lost track of how many times he's been here.

207
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:11,400
Let him in.

208
00:18:14,410 --> 00:18:17,790
I know very well your concerns.

209
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:23,180
However, I don't believe Da Hyeon would be happy with another man.

210
00:18:23,180 --> 00:18:25,090
She would live a more emotionally comfortable life with an average man rather than a chaebol member.

211
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:27,030
There is more to tell you.

212
00:18:27,030 --> 00:18:31,590
We broke up before this decision and tried to forget each other but it was very hard.

213
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:33,300
It didn't make us emotionally comfortable at all.

214
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:36,020
So you want to fight me?

215
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:39,430
If I beat you in any battle, will you give me Da Hyeon?

216
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:55,180
Mom, you called him?

217
00:18:55,180 --> 00:18:56,470
Where is Jae In?

218
00:18:56,470 --> 00:18:58,750
Who called who? He came on his own.

219
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:03,110
I never saw you even during school breaks, but look at you flying over here when I said he was here.

220
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:05,190
It's not like that, Mom.

221
00:19:07,570 --> 00:19:09,730
Huh? Oh my!

222
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:14,870
You smell of alcohol!

223
00:19:14,870 --> 00:19:17,520
Jae In, are you okay?

224
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:19,420
Yeah, I'm fine.

225
00:19:19,420 --> 00:19:22,320
I got his approval.

226
00:19:22,320 --> 00:19:23,520
Pardon?

227
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,900
I got his approval.

228
00:19:26,770 --> 00:19:30,820
Let's get married, Kim Da Hyeon.

229
00:20:28,630 --> 00:20:36,830
♫ That you love me and that I'm your only one. If you hug me just like that, ya ya ya ♫

230
00:20:36,830 --> 00:20:45,090
♫ Then everything would change, ya ya ya ♫

231
00:20:46,510 --> 00:20:50,760
Well done! You guys are so good!

232
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:52,090
You've worked hard!

233
00:20:52,090 --> 00:20:55,080
Thank you, bye!

234
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,990
- Bye!
- Bye!

235
00:20:56,990 --> 00:20:58,920
Let's go.

236
00:21:03,180 --> 00:21:05,120
Whew, I'm really tired.

237
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:11,750
Huh? Jae In! You're here.

238
00:21:18,220 --> 00:21:23,530
An official press announcement will be released soon. It'll be a little noisy. Will you be okay?

239
00:21:23,530 --> 00:21:27,750
Well, it's a good thing that school is on break right now. Hopefully the kids won't be so noisy about it.

240
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:29,500
Who knows?

241
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:33,840
Can you maybe quit and take good care of our future kid—

242
00:21:38,150 --> 00:21:39,910
Oh, I just remembered!

243
00:21:42,370 --> 00:21:45,590
Aren't we going to do a prenup?

244
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:50,590
Of course we do. I'll even have it notarized by a lawyer for sure.

245
00:21:50,590 --> 00:21:53,610
What are you going to lie about this time?

246
00:21:53,610 --> 00:21:55,050
No divorce is allowed.

247
00:21:55,050 --> 00:21:58,420
Until we get old and die, no matter what. It's for life.

248
00:21:58,420 --> 00:22:02,130
Shouldn't we think about that a bit more? Who knows what will happen?

249
00:22:02,130 --> 00:22:06,130
This is non-negotiable. I can't yield on this, so you give up.

250
00:22:06,130 --> 00:22:12,120
Not that kind of stuff. Should we write in something about giving up money or alimony?

251
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:15,350
Why do we need such things? I told you there would be no divorce anyway.

252
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,780
So I have a favor to ask.

253
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:26,440
Please don't abandon me but live with me.

254
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,100
Have a seat here.

255
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:49,200
Teacher Kim Da Hyeon, will you marry me?
(speaking formally)

